The paper deals with linear codes and their applications in cryptography, which are topics that fall under information theory (cs.IT) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses constructions and properties of codes, which are relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of codes in semi-simple group algebras, which is related to representation theory and algebraic structures (cs.SI).
